intro: Jaborosa caulescens var. caulescens, commonly known as the slender jaborosa, is a flowering plant native to South America. It belongs to the Asteraceae family, characterized by its composite flower heads. The plant typically grows as an annual herb with slender, branching stems and narrow, lance-shaped leaves. Its flowers are small and yellow, arranged in clusters, and it produces small, oval-shaped seeds. It is often found in disturbed soils and open habitats, thriving in temperate climates.
